Key operational design of Jiji:

It is primarily a classified ads platform, similar to Craigslist.

Buyers and sellers contact each other directly (call/chat).

Payment and delivery happen outside the platform. 

This is exactly why trust friction and scams are common complaints on such platforms.

2. Why Escrow Integration Is Hard on Jiji
Because there is no transaction layer, you cannot easily insert escrow into the purchase flow.

Typical marketplace flow:

Listing → Checkout → Payment → Delivery → Release funds
Jiji flow:

Listing → Chat/Call → Meet offline → Pay offline
Your escrow system would need to intercept the process before the offline transaction, which the platform does not control.

