Here’s a comprehensive framework to handle these issues:

1. Multi-Layer Verification System
To prevent fake goods or misrepresented specifications, the platform needs verification at multiple points:

Verification Layer	What It Does	Implementation
Seller Verification	Ensures the seller is real and trustworthy	National ID, BVN, bank account verification
Product Verification	Confirms that listed product matches description	Supplier-provided certificates, images, videos, serial numbers
Pre-Delivery Inspection	Confirms that shipped goods meet specs	Driver or 3rd-party verifier checks and uploads photo/video
Post-Delivery Buyer Confirmation	Confirms buyer received correct product	Buyer verification via app: photos, rating form, optional inspection video
Notes:

For high-value items (like 10kW lithium batteries), require serial number verification or QR code scanning.

For electronics or solar panels, integrate a manufacturer or supplier database to validate authenticity.

2. Digital Escrow Conditional Logic
Escrow can now release funds only if verification passes.

Pseudo-code:

if buyer_confirms_product and product_verified:
    release_funds(seller)
elif dispute_raised:
    hold_funds()
    initiate_arbitration()
elif timeout_reached and no_dispute:
    partial_release()
Partial release is useful if:

Minor specification difference (e.g., 7.5kW vs 10kW)

Buyer accepts discount or partial refund

3. Product Dispute Classification
Introduce dispute types in your platform:

Type	Example	Resolution Strategy
Fake item	Seller ships counterfeit battery	Full refund, seller penalized, update seller rating
Specification mismatch	Buyer orders 10kW, receives 7.5kW	Partial refund or return; seller rating updated
Damaged during delivery	Battery damaged en route	Driver liability, escrow holds funds until replacement
Buyer fraud	Buyer claims damage without evidence	Require proof (photo/video/inspection)
Escrow rules enforce conditional payments according to dispute type.

4. Mandatory Evidence Collection
For sensitive goods, require evidence at each stage:

Seller uploads product photos & serial number

Driver confirms shipment & uploads images/videos

Buyer receives product and uploads verification

AI or admin checks consistency before releasing escrow

