5. AI-Based Product Verification
AI can automatically detect fake product claims or misrepresented specs:

Image recognition for branded products or packaging

Text recognition to validate serial numbers

Weight/size validation based on uploaded images

Cross-check with supplier or manufacturer database

Benefits:

Reduces manual verification cost

Detects high-risk sellers quickly

Protects buyers and platform reputation

6. Rating and Reputation Integration
Product disputes feed directly into seller reputation:

Fake or misrepresented goods → rating penalty

Minor mistakes with resolution → small deduction

Perfect execution → rating boost

Over time, buyers, suppliers, and lenders will only engage with high-rated participants, creating a self-regulating system.

7. Arbitration and Resolution Workflow
For unresolved disputes:

Automated evaluation (AI + uploaded evidence)

Manual review (human moderator) for complex cases

Decision:

Refund buyer

Pay seller partially

Penalize seller (e.g., temporary suspension)

Update reputation scores

Escrow funds cannot be released until resolution, protecting all parties.

8. Pre-Approved Supplier Inventory
For items like solar batteries, allow suppliers to pre-register products with specs and serial numbers:

Verified suppliers only

Each listing carries a verified badge

Any changes require supplier approval

Buyers can filter only verified products

This reduces fraud risk upstream.

9. Optional Third-Party Verification Network
For high-value or sensitive goods:

Third-party verification agents can inspect products physically or via video

Fees can be shared between seller, buyer, or escrow system

Agents receive rating themselves to maintain trust

